{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Perfect","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.Polish","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.CantorScheme"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L321-L327","name":"IsClosed.exists_nat_bool_injection_of_not_countable","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#IsClosed.exists_nat_bool_injection_of_not_countable","doc":"Any closed uncountable subset of a Polish space admits a continuous injection\nfrom the Cantor space `ℕ → Bool`."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L265-L314","name":"Perfect.exists_nat_bool_injection","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.exists_nat_bool_injection","doc":"Any nonempty perfect set in a complete metric space admits a continuous injection\nfrom the Cantor space, `ℕ → Bool`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L247-L258","name":"Perfect.small_diam_splitting","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.small_diam_splitting","doc":"A refinement of `Perfect.splitting` for metric spaces, where we also control\nthe diameter of the new perfect sets. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L203-L214","name":"exists_perfect_nonempty_of_isClosed_of_not_countable","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#exists_perfect_nonempty_of_isClosed_of_not_countable","doc":"Any uncountable closed set in a second countable space contains a nonempty perfect subset."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L167-L199","name":"exists_countable_union_perfect_of_isClosed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#exists_countable_union_perfect_of_isClosed","doc":"The **Cantor-Bendixson Theorem**: Any closed subset of a second countable space\ncan be written as the union of a countable set and a perfect set."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L141-L160","name":"Perfect.splitting","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.splitting","doc":"Given a perfect nonempty set in a T2.5 space, we can find two disjoint perfect subsets.\nThis is the main inductive step in the proof of the Cantor-Bendixson Theorem. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L130-L136","name":"Perfect.closure_nhds_inter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.closure_nhds_inter","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L115-L127","name":"preperfect_iff_perfect_closure","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#preperfect_iff_perfect_closure","doc":"In a T1 space, being preperfect is equivalent to having perfect closure."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L103-L111","name":"Preperfect.perfect_closure","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Preperfect.perfect_closure","doc":"The closure of a preperfect set is perfect.\nFor a converse, see `preperfect_iff_perfect_closure`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L94-L98","name":"Preperfect.open_inter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Preperfect.open_inter","doc":"The intersection of a preperfect set and an open set is preperfect. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L89-L90","name":"preperfect_iff_nhds","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#preperfect_iff_nhds","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L86-L86","name":"Perfect.acc","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.acc","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L85-L85","name":"Perfect.closed","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.closed","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L84-L84","name":"Perfect.mk","kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect.mk","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L84-L86","name":"Perfect","kind":"structure","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Perfect","doc":"A set `C` is called perfect if it is closed and all of its\npoints are accumulation points of itself.\nNote that we do not require `C` to be nonempty."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L77-L78","name":"Preperfect","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#Preperfect","doc":"A set `C` is preperfect if all of its points are accumulation points of itself.\nIf `C` is nonempty and `α` is a T1 space, this is equivalent to the closure of `C` being perfect.\nSee `preperfect_iff_perfect_closure`."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.lean#L65-L71","name":"AccPt.nhds_inter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Perfect.html#AccPt.nhds_inter","doc":"If `x` is an accumulation point of a set `C` and `U` is a neighborhood of `x`,\nthen `x` is an accumulation point of `U ∩ C`. "}]}